                  </hi>. I live at the King's Arms, Elephant-street, Rother<lb></lb>hithe; the prisoner lodged in the same house. On Saturday morning I missed my waistcoat and trowsers—I spoke to the prisoner about it on Saturday evening—he said he had taken them, and pawned them—I never permitted him to do so—he said he would return them at some future time—I found these clothes at the pawnbroker's—they are mine.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> If you thought I did not mean to return them, why did you not give me in charge when the coat went four or five weeks before? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> There was a blue coat taken before, which I forgave him for.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">JURY</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Have you been on intimate terms with him? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—we have not associated together—we did not sleep together.</p>
